title: Man from Space
description: Sonny and Skippy are in the park when they hear an explosion in the air. They come across an unconscious pilot who has ejected from a plane. When Sonny gets into difficulty, he sends Skippy to get help.

title: Poachers
description: Skippy sounds the alarm when three men try to steal some Koalas from the Waratah National Park for Dr. Stark's private zoo.

title: Sports Car Rally
description: A sports car club receive permission to run a rally through the Waratah National Park, to Matt's disgust.

title: The Golden Reef
description: Sonny and Skippy discover two geologists diving on a reef in Waratah National Park. The geologists suspect that gold may have washed down the river and collected on the reef. Two criminals watch from afar, waiting for a chance to pounce.

title: Long Way Home
description: Doctor Stark offers Matt $1000 to buy Skippy, then attempts to kidnap her after he refuses.

title: Cage of Koalas
description: Dr Steiner arrives at Waratah National Park to undertake research on the koala population but immediately clashes with Ranger Hammond by insisting on keeping the koalas in cages.

title: The Lyre Bird
description: Skippy leads Sonny to an aspiring young ballerina who has been studying the dance of the lyrebird. When the lyrebird mimics an old man coughing, they search for a botanist who has been missing in the Waratah National Park for a few days.

title: Dead or Alive
description: A mysterious disease threatens to wipe out all animals in the Waratah National Park, and Skippy is suspected of being the carrier.

title: The Marine Biologist
description: Mark is annoyed when Ranger Hammond insists he spends the day assisting a marine biologist that is visiting the park. He changes his mind once he meets Dr Trout. Sonny and Skippy get into trouble while fishing.

title: No Time for Clancy
description: Clarissa "Clancy" Merrick arrives at the Waratah National Park to board with the Hammonds, but soon gets into trouble.

title: Time and Tide
description: Clancy borrows Dr Steiner's camera but gets into trouble taking photos down by the river. The boys race to rescue her before the tide comes in.

title: Can You Keep a Secret?
description: After Clancy keeps a secret for Sonny, he agrees to take her up to visit his secret cave. There they get caught up in the escape plans of a desperate criminal.

title: The Swagman
description: A swagman passing through Waratah National Park strikes up a friendship with Sonny and makes Ranger Hammond question his assumptions.

title: The Honeymooners
description: When Sonny befriends a couple on their honeymoon in the National Park, the wife takes a real shine to Skippy. Soon it becomes clear she wants more from Skippy than friendship.

title: Many Happy Returns
description: Sonny gets his birthday wish when he flies with Jerry in the helicopter, but it takes an unexpected turn.

title: My Best Friend
description: Mark and Clancy try to help Sonny get good marks at school when they substitute his painting of Skippy with their own, but they create a dilemma when it is entered in a competition that attracts an international art critic's attention.

title: When the Bough Breaks
description: Skippy rescues a three-month old baby from drowning in a river.

title: The Waratah Festival
description: A diamond thief has to join the Waratah National Park's float in the Sydney Waratah Festival procession in order to retrieve a stolen bracelet that Skippy picked up after he dropped it.

title: Summer Storm
description: A huge storm sees the team from ranger headquarters involved in some dangerous rescues.

title: The Rustlers
description: Sonny takes a job with a team of sheep shearers to earn money for a present for his father's birthday, unaware that the men are actually rustlers who intend to steal the wool.

title: Double Trouble
description: An actor hired by Dr. Stark attempts to discredit Matt while impersonating him by running a car containing his boss and a Government Senator off the road.

title: Trapped
description: Dr. Stark gets one of his henchmen to impersonate zoologist Professor Lewis. Armed with a mace gun disguised as a camera, the henchman attempts to steal some female anteaters for breeding in Dr. Stark's private zoo.

title: They're Singing Me Back
description: A young aboriginal woman with a beautiful singing voice is pulled between her dream to further her singing career and the call of her elders to return to her people.

title: Tara: Part 1
description: While exploring a cave, Sonny and Skippy find a secret entrance to a valley that was thought to be uninhabited and inaccessible. There, Sonny befriends Tara, an old Aboriginal man living happily on his own.

title: Tara: Part 2
description: When aboriginal elder Tara mistakes Jerry's helicopter as a portent of death, Sonny and Matt seek help to stop him dying.

title: Surf King
description: With some help from Mark, Jerry makes an attempt to overcome injuries he sustained while rescuing a swimmer in trouble and win the main race at a surf carnival. Matt and Clancy are kept busy troubleshooting at the Waratah National Park.

title: The Runaway
description: A boy who has escaped from a youth correctional centre causes havoc in Waratah National Park.

title: The Last Chance
description: A film is being made in Waratah National Park. When the producers decide to include Skippy, she upstages all the human actors.

title: No Trespassers
description: A father and son boxing team set up camp in Waratah National Park to prepare for a big fight. When his son gets into a dangerous situation, the father is forced to realize what is really important.

title: Mayday: Part 1
description: Helicopter pilot Jerry plans to break the rules and visit a girl while on patrol. Before he gets a chance, he gets into trouble investigating a plume of smoke in the park.

title: Mayday: Part 2: Where There's Smoke
description: Jerry survives the helicopter crash but then has to face the music.

title: Date in Dalmar
description: While returning to Ranger Headquarters to meet Sir Adrian Gillespie, Matt, Sonny and Skippy stop to help a man who appears to be lying injured on the road, but the man produces a gun and orders Matt to drive him 80 miles to Dalmar.

title: The Empty Chair
description: When a mining company gets permission to search for oil in Waratah National Park, Sonny realizes that his swag-man friend, Mr Trundle, may be able to help.

title: Ten Little Visitors
description: Ten children from all over the world arrive for a tour of Waratah National Park and Sonny is appointed as their tour guide.

title: Aunt Evelyn
description: The Hammonds' Aunt Evelyn visits the park and tries to convince Matt that Sydney is a better place to raise a young boy than the dangerous wilderness.

title: The Bushrangers
description: While left alone at Ranger Headquarters, Jerry is overpowered by burglars who steal everything that they can move. When Sonny and Skippy come across a group of people dressed like Ned Kelly, Sonny thinks they could be the burglars.

title: Be Our Guest
description: Clancy's mother is expected at Waratah National Park to check on how her daughter is going, but Clancy gets hopelessly lost after she is thrown off her horse, and is followed by a group of Aborigines.

title: The Long Night
description: Mark is accused of a hit-and-run accident that leaves a man badly injured, but the police who arrive to investigate are really industrial spies attempting to cover their tracks.

title: View Matt
description: Sonny overhears Matt receiving advice from his doctor to re-marry, and answers a woman's lonely hearts newspaper advertisement in Matt's name.

title: The Raft
description: Sonny and Skippy sail a home-made raft down the river and rescue a runaway boy from a mangrove swamp.

title: The Perfect Hosts
description: While Matt and Mark are helping out a ranger who has broken down in a downpour near a swollen creek, Sonny and Clancy receive a visitor who matches a radio news report's description of an escaped robber.

title: Honest Jack
description: The team at Ranger Headquarters are surprised to find someone is selling off land in the National Park.

title: Follow My Leader
description: Clancy invites Norman Dupree, a friend of her family and a talented violinist, to lunch at Ranger Headquarters.

title: Tex 'N Ranger
description: Sonny and Skippy see a man get kicked off a cliff.

title: Chicken
description: An unknown illness starts striking down animals in Waratah National Park, including Skippy.

title: Belinda
description: Sonny looks after a show horse, found in the park. When the mean owner turns up, Sonny finds it hard to give her back.

title: The Mine
description: An old Army friend of Matt's arrives at the Waratah National Park to help him blow up an abandoned mine.

title: Rockslide
description: A young deserter from the National Service causes a rock-slide that injures Sonny, and then risks recapture to look after him at Ranger Headquarters.

title: Hide and Seek
description: A childhood friend of Jerry's asks him for refuge in the Waratah National Park.

title: Flying Saucers
description: While taking pictures of Skippy, Sonny sees and photographs what he thinks is a flying saucer.

title: Esmeralda
description: After having his palm read by a gypsy staying in the park, Sonny fears for Matt's life.

title: Puppets
description: A young puppeteer camping in the park may be the answer to raising funds for the RSPCA.

title: Vice Versa
description: Sir Adrian Gillespie brings Professor Leonard Clifton to Waratah National Park so he can take Skippy to a laboratory to study her and find out what makes her so intelligent.

title: Oats
description: An aggressive National Parks & Wildlife Service inspector arrives at the Waratah National Park determined to instill fear into everyone at Ranger Headquarters.

title: The Black Spider
description: Sonny's been reading a lurid novel about blackmailers and he spots Clancy crying after reading a letter, he becomes convinced that his young friend has received a note from someone demanding money.

title: Tread Softly
description: A released prisoner sets traps in the Waratah National Park, forcing its temporary closure.

title: The Shark Taggers
description: Sonny and Skippy help a young scientist with her research of the Port Jackson shark.

title: Surprise! Surprise!
description: Mark plans a surprise birthday party for Clancy.

title: Marco Polo
description: Mark plans an overseas trip for himself and Bob Raine.

title: The Wombat
description: Sonny is trying to study for school exam when Skippy takes him to a baby wombat whose mother has disappeared. He takes it back to ranger headquarters where chaos ensues when Mark tries to take him to quarantine.

title: Axeman
description: The Hammonds are plagued by lumberjacks illegally chopping down trees on National Park land.

title: Up and Beyond
description: Two hot-air balloonists bail out over the Waratah National Park.

title: Round-Up
description: When Sonny and Skippy discover a herd of wild horses damaging vegetation in the Waratah National Park, Matt enlists the aid of two champion rodeo riding brothers to capture them.

title: The Hikers
description: Two schoolteachers go on a dangerous hike in the Loftus Valley.

title: For My Next Trick
description: An itinerant entertainer visits the Waratah National Park while en route to Collingdale.

title: A Bird in the Hand
description: Jerry goes to Sydney Airport to meet a visiting ornithologist, who turns out to be a lovely young nun. Mark finds a person trying to poach some birds from the Waratah National Park.

title: Marathon
description: When the local athletics association hold a cross-country marathon that passes through the Waratah National Park, Mark decides to take part.

title: The Best Man
description: Jerry is asked by a friend to be the best man at a wedding, but can he make it to the church on time?

title: Plain Jane
description: Jane, a friend of Clancy's and a shy country girl, struggles to fit in when she visits Ranger Headquarters.

title: Hi Fi
description: Mark builds himself a hi fi stereo set, for which he finds an unexpected use during a storm.

title: Maggie
description: When Maggie Roderick becomes embroiled with smugglers, she turns to her boyfriend Jerry King for help.

title: Mixed Company
description: An elderly ornithologist is determined to prevent a group of young water skiers from using the river and scaring off the birds he is recording the sounds of.

title: Treasure Hunt
description: There has been a bank robbery and the two robbers have hidden the money in a treasure chest in Matt's car. The chest should contain the prize for a treasure hunt being organised for children in Waratah National Park by the rangers.

title: The Sport of Kings
description: Sir Adrian Gillespie enters a horse in the Corinthian Handicap, a race for male amateur jockeys, at Royal Randwick. Skippy places a $1 bet on a horse with odds of 33:1.

title: Bon Voyage
description: Clancy sits her final music examinations. Sir Adrian Gillespie brings an English visitor to the Waratah National Park to discuss an exchange program with Matt.

title: Cobber
description: Sonny and Skippy become involved in a bitter feud between two old, hard-headed bushmen when they see one of them practising a sheep-dog trial in the Waratah National Park.

title: Tiger
description: An amateur photographer shows Mark and Sonny some photos of an unusual animal, which Matt thinks could be the long-extinct Tasmanian tiger.

title: Luna Park
description: Sonny wins a trip for himself and a friend to Luna Park in a newspaper competition.

title: A Work of Art
description: Skippy makes friends with a famous, yet eccentric, wildlife painter who comes to the Waratah National Park on a commission from Sir Adrian Gillespie.

title: A Manner of Speaking
description: Mark accidentally releases a herd of Mr. Fiorini's cows, and tries to make amends by learning Italian.

title: The Prince of Siam
description: Sonny gets a job with a local gardener so he can earn some pocket money to donate to charity. Skippy asks his bush friends to help search for a lost cat.

title: El Toro
description: An echidna frightens a bull, causing it to run amok in the Waratah National Park during a holiday weekend.

title: Mr. Duffy
description: A strange Irishman bemuses the Hammonds by mending their shoes seemingly in the twinkling of an eye.

title: The Medicine Man
description: Sonny is not feeling well and Matt asks a friend to pick up some medicine in town. However, he gives Sonny some horse medicine instead. At the same time, Sonny fills the ranger station with animals causing chaos.

title: The Veteran
description: An abandoned sports-car leads Matt to a psychotic war hero who thinks he's back in Burma.

title: The Rainmakers
description: A pilot with a cloud-seeding plane, an eccentric old inventor and a young Aborigine all make their own attempts to put an end to a dry spell that has hit the Waratah National Park.

title: Up the Waratahs
description: Two con men try to eliminate Mark Hammond, the local rugby union team's captain, from the competition final.

title: Merry-Go-Round
description: Sonny visits a travelling carnival and meets a young girl who wants to be a clown. Skippy takes an interest in a wooden kangaroo on the carnival's merry-go-round.

title: Pigeon Pair
description: Skippy leads the Hammonds to a pigeon racing clock. When Mark and Sonny return the clock to its rightful owner, eccentric spinster Hattie Dougall, she invites them for tea and shows them a pigeon she plans to race in the Nationals against one from her next door neighbour, a retired colonel.

title: Fred
description: After buying some wildflowers from a local florist who boasts that they have been freshly picked from the Waratah National Park, a furious Sir Adrian Gillespie orders the Hammonds to investigate. Matt thinks it could be the work of a person that they know only as "Fred".
